.TH "SL" "1" "2026" "sl v2026.3" "sl"
.SH NAME
sl \- sl runs across your terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]sl\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
[\f[I]version\f[R]|\f[I]subcommand\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]sl\f[R] is a wrapper script that dispatches to versioned sl
binaries.
When you mistype \f[B]ls\f[R], a steam locomotive runs across your
terminal as a gentle punishment.
.PP
Four versions are available: \f[B]1985\f[R] (the original),
\f[B]2010\f[R], \f[B]2023\f[R], and \f[B]2026\f[R].
Without a version argument, the latest available version is selected
automatically.
.PP
The \f[B]2026\f[R] version detects existing text on the terminal screen
and begins sweeping (pushing text off via the \f[B]dch2\f[R] terminal
capability) only when the train reaches it, preserving text that the
train has not yet passed.
The train enters gradually from beyond the right edge of the screen,
like the original 1985 version.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
The 2026 version captures the terminal screen content to detect existing
text.
This feature currently supports the following terminal emulators on
macOS:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]iTerm2\f[R] (iTerm.app)
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Apple Terminal\f[R] (Terminal.app)
.PP
On unsupported terminals or platforms, the train always sweeps
(equivalent to the 2023 behavior).
Other versions (1985, 2010, 2023) work on any terminal.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R]
Show debug information on the last line before running.
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R]
Dry run.
Show debug information and exit without running the train.
.SH OPTIONS (2026 only)
.TP
\f[B]\-c\f[R], \f[B]\-\-color\f[R]=\f[I]MODE\f[R]
Set color mode: \f[B]truecolor\f[R], \f[B]24bit\f[R], or \f[B]256\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-p\f[R], \f[B]\-\-param\f[R]=\f[I]KEY\f[R]=\f[I]VALUE\f[R]
Set coupler parameter (see COUPLERS for available keys).
.SS Sweep
.TP
\f[B]\-w\f[R]/\f[B]\-W\f[R], \f[B]\-\-sweep\f[R]/\f[B]\-\-no\-sweep\f[R]
Enable or disable the sweep effect (default: on).
.TP
\f[B]\-a\f[R], \f[B]\-\-all\f[R]
Sweep the entire screen instead of just the 7\-line train area.
.TP
\f[B]\-s\f[R]/\f[B]\-S\f[R], \f[B]\-\-stop\f[R]/\f[B]\-\-no\-stop\f[R]
Stop or don\(aqt stop the train at existing text (default: off).
.SS Streak
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R]/\f[B]\-T\f[R], \f[B]\-\-streak\f[R]/\f[B]\-\-no\-streak\f[R]
Enable or disable the streak effect on the bottom row (default: on).
.TP
\f[B]\-p STREAK=\f[R]{\f[B]rumble\f[R],\f[B]reverse\f[R]}
Set streak mode.
\f[B]rumble\f[R] enables thickness modulation, \f[B]reverse\f[R]
reverses the direction.
Combine with commas (e.g., \f[B]\-p STREAK=rumble,reverse\f[R]).
.SH VERSIONS
.TP
\f[B]1985\f[R]
The original SL, written in K&R C with curses.
Output is filtered through a per\-character delay for a retro feel.
.TP
\f[B]2010\f[R]
Updated version using direct terminal control instead of curses.
.TP
\f[B]2023\f[R]
Unicode art version with box\-drawing characters.
Always sweeps text from the left edge.
.TP
\f[B]2026\f[R]
Screen\-aware version.
Detects text on the terminal and sweeps only when the train reaches it.
Enters from beyond the right edge of the screen to preserve right\-side
text.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
These subcommands are primarily for debugging the screen capture and
sweep detection mechanism.
.TP
\f[B]capture\f[R]
Dump the captured visible screen text to stdout.
.TP
\f[B]sweep\-area\f[R]
Show the 7\-line area where the train runs.
.TP
\f[B]clear\-col\f[R]
Print the column number where sweeping should start.
.TP
\f[B]debug\f[R]
Show detailed sweep area analysis with visual output.
.TP
\f[B]mark\f[R]
Draw a visual marker at the sweep start column and print the column
number.
.SH COUPLERS
Couplers are pluggable effect modules for the 2026 version.
Each coupler can be disabled by setting its SL_CAR variable to 0.
Coupler\-specific parameters can be set with the \f[B]\-p\f[R] option
(e.g., \f[B]\-p STREAK=rumble,reverse\f[R]).
.SS Sweep
The sweep coupler deletes characters at the left edge as the train
passes.
Set \f[B]SL_CAR_SWEEP=0\f[R] to disable.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]SL_SWEEP_COL\f[R] \(em Column at which sweeping begins.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]SL_STOP_COL\f[R] \(em Column at which the train stops.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]SL_SWEEP_ALL\f[R] \(em Sweep all screen lines instead of just the
train area.
.SS Streak
The streak coupler draws a glowing light bar on the bottom row.
Set \f[B]SL_CAR_STREAK=0\f[R] to disable.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]SL_STREAK_RUMBLE\f[R] \(em Enable ▔/▀ thickness modulation.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]SL_STREAK_REVERSE\f[R] \(em Reverse direction (left\-to\-right).
.SH TERMINAL TIPS
The 2026 version uses Unicode box\-drawing and block characters whose
East Asian Width property is \(dqAmbiguous\(dq.
Terminals that treat ambiguous\-width characters as double\-width will
cause visual glitches (line wrapping / \(dqderailment\(dq).
Make sure to uncheck this setting:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]iTerm2\f[R]: Profiles → Text → Unicode → \f[B]Ambiguous characters
are double\-width\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Apple Terminal\f[R]: Profiles → Advanced → \f[B]Unicode East Asian
Ambiguous characters are wide\f[R]
